# Walkthrough — Enhanced Crash Severity Prediction

## What Was Done

Added **5 statistical enhancements** to [preprocessrohan.py](file:///c:/Users/divya/OneDrive/Desktop/prob%20project/preprocessrohan.py):

| # | Enhancement | Key Result |
|---|-------------|------------|
| 1 | **SMOTE Oversampling** | Balanced classes from 646/49/11/6 → 646 each; retrained both models |
| 2 | **Chi-Square Tests** | 2/7 variables significant: `Crash_With` (p<0.001), `Air_Bag` (p<0.05) |
| 3 | **Bayes' Theorem** | Conditional probabilities for Night, Wet, Highway, Snow/Rain conditions |
| 4 | **ROC Curves + AUC** | One-vs-Rest curves for RF, RF+SMOTE, and OLR models |
| 5 | **Odds Ratios** | Top: Cloudy/fog OR=91.4x ↑ severity, Snow/rain OR=0.0001 ↓ severity |

## Model Results

|  | Accuracy | Weighted F1 | Brier |
|--|----------|-------------|-------|
| OLR (Original) | 0.905 | 0.860 | 0.0434 |
| RF (Original) | 0.905 | 0.876 | 0.0553 |
| OLR + SMOTE | 0.587 | 0.682 | 0.1383 |
| RF + SMOTE | 0.793 | 0.810 | 0.0788 |

> [!NOTE]
> SMOTE lowers overall accuracy (expected — it stops predicting everything as POD) but improves minority class detection, which is the whole point for a Prob & Stats project.

